President Biden and Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau had a conversation regarding several important topics. They discussed preparations for the upcoming Leaders Summit on Climate, efforts to combat the COVID-19 pandemic, and the unjust detention of two Canadians, Michael Kovrig and Michael Spavor, by the Chinese government. President Biden praised Canada's contributions in addressing climate change and both leaders reaffirmed their commitment to global leadership on the climate crisis through the U.S.-Canada High-Level Dialogue on Climate Ambition. They also agreed to continue collaborating on controlling the pandemic, public health responses, global health security, and ensuring global access to COVID-19 vaccines. President Biden expressed condemnation for the arbitrary detention of Kovrig and Spavor and reiterated the United States' support for Canada in securing their release.